    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
      <p>The Hundley collection consists of eleven bound volumes,
         including ledgers, daybooks, an invoice book and a letter
         book, 1834-1900, concerning Larkin Hundley's general store at
         Montagues Post Office in Essex County, Virginia. Montagues,
         located in the southern part of the county two miles from the
         Rappahannock River, had a population of fifty persons in 1835,
         including an attorney and a physician, according to Joseph
         Martin's Gazeteer of 1835.</p>
    </scopecontent>
